      "content": "alright, i'll grab that telemetry. but looking at the migration plan, the cloud transition is going to be on a much higher latency connection. i'm worried that if we wipe the local instance too fast, the sudden switch might cause some gaps in the monitoring stream or even lead to data corruption in the buffer. are you absolutely sure you don't need to run a full diagnostic or a localized check of the sync protocol before we kill the local process? i'd rather be safe than lose the stream.",
